Message:If there's one thing I've learned in life...it's that if you're truly passionate about something, do not let anything stop you. Test scores should not define you and I will not let them define me. I really am passionate about wanting to become a nurse and I am not going to let anything stop me. Yes, I've had to retake some classes and still have a few to take, but over this experience I've really learned and now value the importance of education and personal growth. ID:639792165_10153080829602166
Name:Welcome Back, Tar Heels
Story:N/A
Message:As many of you know, I just started my senior year at UNC-Chapel Hill. While I'm excited and proud of my accomplishments, I'm also incredibly melancholy - I had no idea that every "last" would be so bittersweet (I don't even want to know what graduation is going to feel like!) I feel like someone trying to keep water from running out of cupped hands... Wanting to make every moment count, while desperately trying to make time pass by slower.

If I've learned anything so far, it's that UNC is truly a magical place for so many reasons. I honestly can't imagine attending any other college in the world. I feel like I could go to school here for the next 20 years and still not learn everything that this university has to offer. I'm determined to make senior year count, because there's no place I'd rather be than UNC.

Welcome back from TEDxUNC, Tar Heels, and here's to a wonderful senior year!!

Story:Joo Oh Park added 26 photos.
Message:So this Japanese mofo (Shinnosuke Koyanagi) visited Korea with absolutely no plan...messaging me the very first day saying he couldnt get in the hostel he booked thats a galaxy away from the city center...Please research before you travel anywhere.

His three day trip to Korea consisted of plethora of local Korean experiences...such as sleeping in a love motel (with me), eating raw beef, liver, stomach, Korean barbeque and "four seasons soup" (you don't wanna know), drinking in Gangnam and Itaewon and sightseeing at Hooker Hill (trust me... only sightseeing)... things that you could never get with package tour with your parents.

It was great to see an old friend who spent the time of your life together in our young age. Its also amazing how little we changed...that's brotherhood, man. Now I am looking forward to visiting this dude im the close future.

Cheers bro, thanks for visiting. Also thanks ??? (Hank) who responded faster than anyone and did not hesitate to share the moment with us.

Message:On this day in history:
1698, Peter the Great of Russia levied a tax on beards in an effort to encourage men to shave theirs and thus westernize his country.
1774, The first Continental Congress convened in Philadelphia.
1836, Sam Houston became the first president of Texas, and Texas remained the Lone Star Republic until it was admitted as a state in 1845.
1839, Britain and China fought the First Opium War over British demands to have a monopoly on the opium trade in China.
1905, President Teddy Roosevelt negotiated the Treaty of Portsmouth between Russia and Japan.  TR was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize for his mediation and was the first president to receive the award.
1972, Palestinian terrorists murdered 11 Israeli athletes at the Munich Olympics.
1997, Mother Teresa died in Calcutta.  I was blest to have met her there in 1988.  She is on the fast-track to being designated a saint.

Message:Hi everyone,
We will be leaving our flat on the 1st of September and we are looking for someone to take over. The flat is 36m? with private bathroom and toilets, and we installed an IKEA kitchenette with electric plates and storage. It is part of a house with two neighbourgs, there is a common well furnished kitchen upstairs that you can also use if you want to cook with gas, as well as another bathroom. Washing machine and dryer are provided and free to use. 
The flat is located on Boterdiep, which is less than 5 minutes walking from Martini tower and 10 minutes biking from Zernike. There are lots of shops around (two AH 3 and 5 min walking, Jumbo 5 min walking, Asian shop 7 min walking...). 
The price is 526/month for one person and 50 more for two persons including utilities and internet. It is particularily well suited for a couple, but only allows one registration to the city hall (only a problem if your visa specifies that).
We would like to sell our furnitures for a reasonable price. This includes almost everything seen in the pictures (kitchen block + kitchen ustensiles, big fridge with freezer, closet, table, sofa chairs, oven, vaccum cleaner...).
There is an agency fee of ~516? as well as a deposit of one month rent.
Don't hesitate to PM for more information! Cheers

ID:1081129551_10202724390405821
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

But after I regained awareness (at least where my memory begins, anyway), I was told that I had just cried freely after I woke up and had asked to "hug it out" with my beefy nurse guy. Apparently we hugged for like a whole minute. It's mostly just good to know that I don't act all that different with or without the drugs lol...

Name:Students mourn Fred Clark, longtime advocate for affordability
Story:N/A
Message:Dr. Clark is the co-founder of a program that allowed thousands and thousands of students, including myself, to graduate debt-free from Carolina. He ran that program as it developed from a need-based award to a phenomenal support system for students that I have utilized countless times during my years here. He was always available for advice and help, particularly during the challenging patches of my first and second year and consequently, I owe so much of my success to him and his program. I'm not sure how to express the infinite gratitude I have for someone who made UNC an attainable dream for me, so I will just leave it at this: Carolina truly lost a priceless gem. Rest easy, Dr. Clark.

ID:1390426461_724357697611912
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Hello,
Let's talk about integrity and tournaments. It's really important that every team is portrayed correctly and every person is the skill level they say they are. I understand there are people who do not like to play ranked, but usually I can look at the normal games and see the players they do play against. Some people do make an honest mistake and that is fine, but there are definitely people out there that are purposefully not representing themselves correctly. The whole purpose of the tournaments that UNC LoL hosts is to give people an opportunity to compete with people in the same community on as level a field as possible. We are going through some leadership changes and trying to improve on the tournaments because last year was our first "real year" as a big club. We're growing along with the club and with that it's really important that the integrity of these tournaments is upheld. To continue hosting these events and making them better, honesty is really important.

So this all means a few things:
-- When you sign up please sign up with your highest elo/main/whatever you want to call it account. I want to stress again how important it is to accurately display your skill level when participating in the tournaments. If you are unranked, we will do our best to correctly judge your skill level.
-- You may only play on the account that you registered for the tournament with UNLESS you have gotten explicit permission from the enemy team. It is unfair to use a different account in order to avoid being target banned. If you sign up with summoner "X" you may ONLY USE summoner "X" UNLESS you have spoken to the enemy team and they have agreed to it.
-- If there is enough evidence to show that you did not correctly portray your skill level or have been dishonest in a tournament/during sign-ups, you will be removed from the tournament and banned from future events until you have shown that you have remediated.

tl;dr: Don't fucking cheat or do dishonest shit because we will find out and you will be banned from events. We are not putting up with this type of behavior any longer. This is your warning; there are no second chances.

He has no other offers lined up and virtually all the jobs in his chosen field are gone, so he must now apply for jobs in other fields.
He has completely SNAPPED.
Before he was a goofy, somewhat anxious, yet sweet and funny Chinese guy. After his rejection he has turned into like...a parody of a gangster rapper.
He has started sleeping through all his classes and just being irresponsible in general, and I understand that he is feeling the sting of rejection and might be a bit depressed, but it goes further than that.
He spends 80% of the day in bed watching Lil Wayne videos on YouTube. He googles the lyrics and 'raps' along. When he's not watching the videos, he's 'freestyling'. Basically he says the following phrases over and over again for 20+ minutes at a time
Get bitches, get money
I slay niggas
I get all the pussy
These hoes on my dick
Bitches love my dick
I make every pussy wet
Ima kill a nigga
Basically, variations of that over and over again. I'M NOT JOKING.

He has started referring to me as "bitch"...in a not nice way.
I am really upset and confused because he never acted this way before. I have asked him to stop, told him it's making me sad, breaking my heart and he just won't stop.

Tonight we went out to dinner and he leaned into his drink and made a slurping noise and said "This is what it sounds like when I'm eating all those other bitches' pussies".
WTF. I can't do this for much longer.
Is this relationship salvageable? Was this the kind of guy he was all along and now he is just showing this side because he's stressed/upset about the job?
I'm so sad and I can't take this anymore....

Story:N/A
Message:Hey so tomorrow we will do the Sha Tin Pass Road to Kowloon Reservoir hike. I know the high islands reservoir looks cool, but I just checked and it would take hours to get there because it's on the very western tip of the New Territories with no MTR access. So tomorrow we will meet down in the lobby at 9:30 and head out at 9:45 sharp. The plan is the take the MTR to Wong Tai Sin and get a cheap cab ride to the trail. Bring lots of water and good shoes. See everyone tomorrow!

Here is something to think about : 
Perhaps, most of the misunderstandings derives from lacking a measure on well-devised and approprite inactions rather than overrating showy actions. Hence, the world tends to incentivise actions without prudential foresight which leads to men to operate at a counterfactually inefficient equilibria. Under absence of empirics of men assessing unobservable justice, watchful God, loving family, loyal friends, and warm-hearted acquaintances will be forever misunderstood and tempted to act less prudent. Human stupidity or humanity?

ID:1531609000_10201669923259817
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

This fatal disease affects 350,000 people worldwide. I now nominate Erin Kozlow, Maureen Kozlow, and Barbara Beecroft. ID:100000099849988_830372750309379
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:I've referred to my mom as the moon ever since she passed away. Bright, beautiful, glowing...overseeing. With that, I've become increasingly preoccupied with the sky, so today being another supermoon, I was psyched and walked outside to find it. I could not. The sky was full of clouds and I could only see the light from where the clouds were covering it. I walked the entire neighborhood to find any view of the moon, and on my way back, after an unsuccessful attempt, I received this message: "Though you can't see it, you know it's there. You can feel its presence.  That is myself. Though you cannot see me, I'm always there, watching over you." And needless to say, the clouds opened up and I had a full glimpse of the moon. 

Even on a new moon, when it's not visible to any eye, it is there. It doesn't disappear or go away simply because we can't see it.  My mom hasn't gone anywhere, ya'll.

Story:N/A
Message:Oluwatobi 'Tobi' Alawode nominated me to do this challenge! I did it, but I will also donate!! (AFTER I buy the rest of my textbooks, y'all already know the struggle.)

Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) also known as Lou Gehrig's disease is a fatal neurodegenerative disease. I'm sure a lot of you already know about this disease because of these types of videos. More important, however, is the reason why these videos have been spreading worldwide: lack of funding. Besides ALS, there are many diseases that lack funding for research and helpful treatments for those who suffer with them. If you're an American citizen, you have the amazing privilege to VOTE. Medical research has been cut by BILLIONS due to the federal budget. Being the single largest source of ALS research funding in the world, NIH needs your support as well in order to help those who suffer with these diseases. That way, incurable, fatal diseases can become preventable/treatable (and hopefully nonexistent). 

THAT BEING SAID I NOMINATE Adeola Keku Jassmin Smith and Christina Perkins. Y'all got 24 hours <3

ID:100001043113693_771080102936753
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

Message:Quote: You might claim ? as most people do ? that you have never been influenced by philosophy. I will ask you to check that claim. Have you ever thought or said the following? "Don't be so sure ? nobody can be certain of anything." You got that notion from David Hume (and many, many others), even though you might never have heard of him. Or: "This may be good in theory, but it doesn't work in practice." You got that from Plato. Or: "That was a rotten thing to do, but it's only human, nobody is perfect in this world." You got that from Augustine. Or: "It may be true for you, but it's not true for me." You got it from William James. Or: "I couldn't help it! Nobody can help anything he does." You got it from Hegel. Or: "I can't prove it, but I feel that it's true." You got it from Kant. Or: "It's logical, but logic has nothing to do with reality." You got it from Kant. Or: "It's evil, because it's selfish." You got it from Kant. Have you heard the modern activists say: "Act first, think afterward"? They got it from John Dewey.  http://fare.tunes.org/liberty/library/pwni.html

ID:100001734134044_552285444839255
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:An open letter to the heirs of my body:

When I was a pre adolescent child,  beginning at some undetermined age, but probably around age five, and continuing until age ten, my mother, your grandmother,  Roberta, every Halloween, without fail,  would dress me as a fat woman with a stuffed pillow under my dress giving me the effect of girth.  I would be smeared with lipstick, adorned in blackface,  wiged and ushered out to engage in a hearty round of Trick or Treating.  Why the adornment of blackface?   Only Roberta's maker knows, and she is not telling-at least not yet.

My mother would similarly present herself, would gather an entourage of   neighborhood of Trick or Treating children and like the pied piper, off we went.  There was no shame for Halloween was the one time of the year when it was OK to dress in drag. I enjoyed it.  We got loads of candy.  It was a fun time for all.

Any harmful long term affects of mother dressing her only child as a woman in blackface. 65 years and six children later, I subjectively answer?No.

Any of you have any similar experiences?

Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:The rhythm of the self-oppressed.

Take it, seize it, get up off the floor. For me, I have witnessed, during my lifetime, an instant replay, from many within my greater family, some variation of the theme  ?we are being held down by the man?.  I hold out hope that one day, somehow, someone, or  someones, can capture the imagination of the people to stop seeing themselves as victims, but as bright stars, with endless possibilities.  For those (I am sure well meaning) white supporters, I view you as enablers, if not sycophants.   You do my family no good by promoting our victimization and fostering a since of ?comrades, though we are not among the oppressed, we feel your pain and lend our support". We are 150 years beyond the abolition of slavery, and some fifty years beyond the advent of the civil rights movement.  Enough is enough. Marching in the streets must cease serving as the opiate of the masses.

 If the problem is within  our house, then the solution must come from within our house.  Strangers come to the aid of children.  Adults must fight their own battles, especially when the battle is between themselves.  Take it, seize it, get up off the floor.

Message:Recognition is given that what I am about to say runs counter to an acquired taste.  However, its saying is no less worthy.  If you have something adverse or otherwise unflattering to say to person ?A? about person ?B? and you instruct or caution person ?A? to not disclose it to person ?B? then it is a hard case to make that it should have been said at all.  The better view is that if you do not want to leave any entrails traceable to you then the gossip should have not been disclosed to person ?A? in the first instance.  To whom it may concern, what say you?

Message:Greece is considered the cradle of democracy. Only his ?philosopher kings? were suited for government leadership. I would like to open a dialogue, without being considered elitist, on how Plato?s republic would fair in contemporary America.

ID:100002209942621_622660121150980
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

ID:100002813248009_454019568035147
Name:null
Story:N/A
Message:Today i walked into Teague and saw all the empty rooms and halls. I felt empty. Today was graduation. It's suppose to be a happy day, but somehow i felt sad.   I walked out of the global center after the econ commencement in a hurry without really saying good byes to my friends because i was tired. I didnt realize that this is one of the last few moments we will have together. In a couple of days, we would all depart. Although we all say "keep in touch" and "visit each other often", the ugly truth is that we probably wont. Its not that we dont value our friendship. Its that we are now going into the real world to start our new life and family, and itll be hard to sit back, relax, and reconnect with our old friends from our busy lives.  Throughout these four years, i made some great friends; some with annoying qualities haha. But today, when its time to depart, all i see and remember are the good times we had together, because thats wut really matters.  This last senior year has been crazy. I had so much fun! Thanks guys for a great year! These are the best times i had on college. I really hope that these days can last forever where we just drink and play random games. Thanks guys! Im not gonna wish u guys good luck for ur post graduation lives because i know you guys wont need it. Im gonna wish for us to be able to come back and relive our days together soon! <3

Message:Hi everyone! For those of you who don?t know me, I?m Jacob Etzelmueller and I am running for VP of Educational Enrichment and VP of Member Relations.
I am about to conclude my freshman year here at Madison, and it has been a blast! One part I am particularly thankful for is our Actuarial Science club. I was a direct admit freshman, which allowed me to jump right into the club, serving as the class representative last semester for Act Sci 301 on Wednesdays.  I gained perspective on what it takes to be an officer by learning from the best (our very own current officers Liz Horstmeier Eric Schumann Alyssa Webb Jaime LewisTiffany Lu Li and Dani Beierle) Sitting in on these board meetings as a rep helped me realize how much this club really does for its members and how many people it affects. I have met so many amazing people I never would have met otherwise and had great experiences with them all. 
I would love the opportunity to help give back to this organization by serving on our officer board. I would make sure that our club stays focused on what it always has, promoting interaction between actuaries, helping each other, and providing guidance for what do after we leave this great University. I would appreciate your vote and I can?t wait to see you all there on Tuesday!

ID:100006641705075_712707735416524
Name:null
Story:Katrina Wertz posted an event to Facss China's timeline.
Message:This month of February, Carolina China Network is excited to present a discussion entitled China & Africa: Define the Relationship on Friday, February 28th from 4-5pm in Union Room 3206.  We are keen on exposing students on our campus to the myriad of reasons why China has turned attention to Africa?s continent and what opportunities and consequences have come about.  The short one-hour event will be a great chance to come together and eat free Chinese dumplings and discuss economic, diplomatic, and cultural collaborations from a high-level viewpoint.  Our goal is for each person in the room to hear, share, and learn something new about the Sino-Africa relationship that they may not have heard or considered before, and to meet someone in the room that you could continue the conversation with beyond this event!

2013-09-18 08:47

 

 

 

    ???????

    ???????

 

    ???????????????? ???????????????? ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????

 

 

    Jim Morgan  was named  President  and CEO  of Krispy  Kreme Doughnuts, Inc. in January 2008. Mr. Morgan has been a member of the Krispy  Kreme  Board  of Directors  since  2000  and was elected its Chairman in 2005.

 

    Mr. Morgan served as Chairman and CEO of Wachovia Securities following the acquisition of Interstate/Johnson Lane, Inc. (IJL) by Wachovia  Corporation.   He  also  served  as Chairman  and  CEO of Interstate/Johnson Lane, Inc.. Mr. Morgan is a past member of the Securities Industry Association Board of Directors and the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) regional firms committee, and is currently on the Board of Directors of Coca-Coca Bottling Company Consolidated. Mr. Morgan has more than 40 years of business experience and is a

1969 graduate of Vanderbilt University. He also served as a lieutenant in the U.S. Navy.

 

 

    Friday, Sept. 27, 6:30pm

    ??????????

    UNC Hamilton Hall, Lecture Room 100

    102 Emerson Dr. Chapel Hill NC 27514
